                                                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="14557446" author="gliptak" created="Sat, 23 May 2015 17:48:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=busbey&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;busbey&quot;&gt;Sean Busbey&lt;/a&gt; Please let me know what related changes can be worked.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14557463" author="busbey" created="Sat, 23 May 2015 18:34:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Unfortunately, the only extant issues I know about are listed in subtasks. If you have an account on builds.apache, I&apos;d love help setting up additional jobs to cover java 8. Otherwise, I could use help identifying gaps.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d say the best way to start is to attempt to run through our full build/test suite with java 8 and see if anything falls over (e.g. &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-13569&quot; title=&quot;correct errors reported with mvn site&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-13569&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-13569&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;). Once those are done, try to run any of the integration tests, even just on a single node.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14557473" author="gliptak" created="Sat, 23 May 2015 18:55:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I would be good to work some Jenkins configuration. How do I go about setting up an account on builds.apache?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;PS Trying login to builds.apache&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/federatedLoginService/openid/login?from=%2F&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/federatedLoginService/openid/login?from=%2F&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;with Google displays:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;OpenID auth request contains an unregistered domain: &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/federatedLoginService/openid/finish&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/federatedLoginService/openid/finish&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also myopenid is no longer available as per:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.theregister.co.uk/2013/09/05/myopenid_closes_for_good_2014/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.theregister.co.uk/2013/09/05/myopenid_closes_for_good_2014/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Trying to login with OneUbuntu shows:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Login Error: unassociated null&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;null &quot;null&quot; is not associated with any of the Jenkins user account. Note that if you already have a user account and is trying to associate a null with your account, this is a wrong place. To do so,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Login&lt;br/&gt;
    Click on your name&lt;br/&gt;
    Click on the &quot;Configure&quot; link, and then&lt;br/&gt;
    associate a new null from that page&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14557477" author="busbey" created="Sat, 23 May 2015 19:02:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Getting access to builds.apache requires that you have an ASF committer account (it can be on any project) and then we have to have our PMC chair add you (currently that&apos;s &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=apurtell&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;apurtell&quot;&gt;Andrew Purtell&lt;/a&gt;). (ref the &lt;a href=&quot;http://wiki.apache.org/general/Jenkins#How_do_I_get_an_account&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;ASF Jenkins FAQ&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14557479" author="busbey" created="Sat, 23 May 2015 19:06:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;thanks for the heads up on myopenid. filed BUILDS-82 to have it removed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14557484" author="gliptak" created="Sat, 23 May 2015 19:13:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I also filed BUILDS-83 on the Google issue above.&lt;br/&gt;
At this time, I do not have an ASF committer account ...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14584115" author="gliptak" created="Fri, 12 Jun 2015 21:28:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=busbey&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;busbey&quot;&gt;Sean Busbey&lt;/a&gt; Any identified code changes I can work around this? Thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14584124" author="busbey" created="Fri, 12 Jun 2015 21:32:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll take things for a run tonight and cc you on any created tickets. Sound good?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14584574" author="gliptak" created="Sat, 13 Jun 2015 11:42:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sounds good &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14597170" author="busbey" created="Tue, 23 Jun 2015 04:56:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m running my RC testing on a cluster with JDK8. Is there anything else besides the above additions to our test rig and javadoc/site that folks would like to see before changing jdk8 support to &quot;yes&quot; ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14598869" author="stack" created="Wed, 24 Jun 2015 04:58:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks great &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=busbey&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;busbey&quot;&gt;Sean Busbey&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14608809" author="ndimiduk" created="Tue, 30 Jun 2015 18:28:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Nice work &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=busbey&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;busbey&quot;&gt;Sean Busbey&lt;/a&gt;! I&apos;m excited to see the IT&apos;s running regularly. I think you&apos;re missing the subtask of updating the support matrix in the book &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14608816" author="busbey" created="Tue, 30 Jun 2015 18:30:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;that&apos;s &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-13911&quot; title=&quot;add 1.2 to prereq tables in ref guide&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-13911&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-13911&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Could use a +1 &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/wink.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14610208" author="busbey" created="Wed, 1 Jul 2015 13:15:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s now possible to get through an entire make_rc.sh run with JDK8 as the target JVM, so I&apos;m closing this out. Master and branch-1 are likely to drift from that due to the tighter javadoc requirements until we can get multi-jdk precommit tests in (probably late July), so something to watch out for on later releases.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15063179" author="eclark" created="Fri, 18 Dec 2015 00:36:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We&apos;ve been running 8 on production for a while now. +1 from me.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
